Core Tests
Create a SetMediaClockTimer in HelloSdl and set the forwardSeekIndicator and backSeekIndicator, example below
SetMediaClockTimer mediaClockTimer = new SetMediaClockTimer().countUpFromStartTimeInterval(30, 253,
                                        AudioStreamingIndicator.PAUSE);
SeekStreamingIndicator forward = new SeekStreamingIndicator();
forward.setType(SeekIndicatorType.TIME);
forward.setSeekTime(15);
SeekStreamingIndicator back = new SeekStreamingIndicator();
back.setType(SeekIndicatorType.TIME);
back.setSeekTime(15);
mediaClockTimer.setForwardSeekIndicator(forward);
mediaClockTimer.setBackSeekIndicator(back);
sdlManager.sendRPC(mediaClockTimer);

On the hmi you should see the media seek indicators reflect what was set in the code, update the seekTime property and restart the app to verify the indicators change to reflect the new seekTime. Also update the forwardSeekIndicator and backSeekIndicator to use SeekIndicatorType.TRACK and do not set the seekTime. this time the hmi should show track skip indicators instead of time skip indicators
